collections.name: Inspirations Of Mania Traditional Art
collections.description:
I deal with a lot of stress and anxiety. I used to cope by doing slow light workouts for 4 hours every morning but ended up having to have two disks in my neck removed and the 3 vertebrae fused with a titanium plate and bone grafts. Needless to say, I don't lift weights anymore. Painting and drawing has become my new medium for anxiety, and now physical pain as well since the surgery was not successful in that it has not reduced pain levels (so far anyway, I am still hoping for improvement). So far pain has actually gone up. It did thankfully save the use of my arms and legs though, that I am thankful for. Anyway, inspiration tends to come to me when I am feeling depressed or anxious, sometimes it happens four times in one weekend, other times I go weeks/months/years without a drop of creativity. 
Part of the reason I have my art up for sale is I just want people to see it, so please enjoy even if you do not make a purchase.

collections.name: Celestial Graph
collections.description:
Where does your time flow?

The Celestial Graph is a collection of 200 artworks created by the designer and 3D artist Kahmun Jha.

For centuries, humans have read time through the stars, seeking to define their place in the universe. Celestial Graph continues this exploration, creating abstract pattern from real-time constellation data that shift with the seasons. By mapping celestial coordinates down to specific dates and times, it offers a journey through time’s passage and a sense of transcendence.

Recorded every 12 minutes with 120 movements, these patterns represent the relativity of time between humanity and the cosmos. Each star moves at its own pace — from the steady presence of Polaris to fleeting comets. Celestial Graph captures these rhythms, connecting them to your sense of time.

Colors are derived from light wavelengths captured when constellations reach their highest point. Each piece’s metadata is permanently preserved on Arweave’s Permaweb.

collections.name: Heavenly Skills
collections.description:
Heavenly Skills is an action-adventure game that combines compelling storytelling, martial arts, and a celebration of global cultures. Set in the present day, the game follows the journey of a protagonist who, immune to a world-dominating magic, seeks wisdom in different regions to face an evil force. Each location offers new combat styles, traditional costumes, and unique challenges, highlighting the connection between culture, nature, and strategy.

The realistic combat system, interaction with natural environments, and deep narrative choices make the experience immersive and rewarding. In addition, the game includes a crowdfunding and social impact model, transforming created content into educational materials for young people from vulnerable communities. Heavenly Skills goes beyond entertainment, offering a cultural, emotional, and strategic journey that inspires players to explore and learn while connecting with a world rich in diversity.

collections.name: The Painter
collections.description: This enigmatic middle-aged painter, with a weathered face and a piercing gaze, is no ordinary artist. His rough, paint-stained hands and intense expression reveal a lifetime of hardship and obsession. He stands immersed in his craft, lost in a world of his own creation. But his art is not just paint on canvas—his masterpieces come to life, breaking the boundaries between reality and imagination. Haunted by his past and driven by an insatiable passion, he paints with melancholic intensity, as if each stroke carries a piece of his soul. His mind is consumed by his work; nothing else holds meaning. He is possessed by his vision, unable to escape the relentless pursuit of perfection. His eyes reflect a deep sorrow, yet also a flicker of genius, a spark that fuels his obsession. He is different—detached from the world, living only through his art, where his creations breathe with the echoes of his untold stories.
